---

## Limitations & future work
- Data is synthetic (generated with domain-calibrated parameters); production deployment requires integration with CCTMC sensor feeds or Google Maps Traffic API
- LSTM baseline was trained on shorter sequences (24-step) due to compute constraints; longer context windows may improve temporal modelling
- Spatial autocorrelation between corridors (e.g., Kathipara overflow to GST Road) is not yet modelled — a Graph Neural Network (GNN) is a natural extension
- Weather features could be enriched with rainfall intensity (mm/hr) rather than a binary flag

